{In this position from the Albin's Counter Gambit, Black did not force White
to commit his structure with 7...a5. Now, he tried it} 12... a5 {but White
replied with the simple} 13. O-O {and the game went} axb4 14. axb4 Rxa1 15.
Bxa1 c6 16. Nd2 Qg5 $6 {Black wants at the same time create ideas like Bh3,
and prepare to develop the Bf8. But he is behind in development, and White has
a nice way to take advantage of it. How?} 17. f4 $1 {Taking the initiative, of
course!} Qg4 18. f5 Bd7 19. e4 f6 20. Qa2 $1 {[%cal Ya2a8,Ya2g8] ;Peek,M (2293)
-Vermue,A (1810) Vlissingen HZ op 21st 2017 (1) 1-0 From a2 the queen not only
prevents Black from castling, but also threatens an invasion in the opponent's
camp with decisive effect. Besides, the Black queen is out of play on the
kingside and can't help in the defense. White's advantage is already winning -}
