c1 or d1/e1 and go for d4-d5 at some moment. 2- Advancing the a-pawn with
a4-a5 in order to get rid of his only weakness and leave an isolated pawn in
Black's camp. After checking the recent games, it is possible to understand
that Black has found the right path against both plans. These were the reasons
that made me turn my attention to a direct approach with} 13. d5 $5 {
