[%cal Ye3c5] With every move, Black's position is getting more unpleasant. Now,
the king threatens to invade the weakened queenside.} (27. Ra2 $1 {would be an
interesting preparatory move, preventing Black's next resource}) 27... Nc4+ 28.
Kd4 Nb2 {[%csl Ya4,Yd3] And now White has the tactical idea} 29. axb5 $1 Nxd3
30. b6 $1 {[%cal Yb6b7]} Rab8 31. Nxb8 Rxb8 32. Kxd3 Rxb6 33. Kc4 Ke7 34. Kc5
Rf6 35. Ra3 $14 {Even in this rook endgame, White's position is more active
and easier to play. He managed to win inTregubov,P (2586)-Sychev,K (2445)
RUS-chT rapid 2016 (5.5) 1-0} *

