O-O-O $1 {[%cal Yd1d8] a very strong idea} Kc6 $8 {The king's dance begins} (
12... axb5 13. Bb4+ $1 Ke8 14. Bxf8 Kxf8 15. Rd8+ Ke7 16. Rxc8 Kd7 17. Rc5 $18)
13. Na5+ Kb6 14. Nc4+ $1 Kxb5 15. Nd6+ Kc5 16. Nxc8 Ne7 (16... Nc6 {[%csl Gc8]
runs into a nice refutation} 17. b4+ $1 Nxb4 18. Kb1 $3 $18 {[%cal Rd1c1]}) 17.
Kb1 $1 Nxc8 18. Rc1+ Kd6 19. Rxc8 Kd7 20. Rc1 {and White keeps a clear
advantage} Nc6 21. Bc4 f6 22. Rhd1 $16) (6... a6 $2 {Black is playing with the
fire.} 7. Nb3 Qc7 8. Nd5 Qd6 9. Be3 Nd7 10. Rc1 $19 {It is really impressive
that White managed to lose this position -Kukovec,B (2083)-Orel,O (2305) Bled
op 22nd 2001 (5) 0-1}) 7. Bd2 $5 {Despite being the third most played move, it
seems very logical since White continues developing and creating threats
against the queen. White's high score with this move suggests that Black has
some unpleasant problems to solve.} e5 (7... Qb6 {Maiorov,N (2541)-Stephan,V 
(2353) Avoine op 31st 2016 (4) 1-0} 8. Rc1 $1 Bd7 9. Nb3 e5 10. e4 Bb4 11. Be3
Qd8 12. Bd3 O-O 13. O-O {[%cal Yc3d5]} Bc6 14. Qe2 Nbd7 15. Rfd1 a6 (15... Qe7
16. a3 Bxc3 17. Rxc3 $16) (15... Bxc3 16. Rxc3 Bxe4 $2 17. Bxe4 Nxe4 18. Rcd3
Nef6 19. Nc5 $18)) (7... Bd7 {Wirthensohn,H (2395) -Steiger,W Oberliga Baden
